article.description: DeWanna Bonner scored a game-high 29 points and Sherell Hobbs added 20 to lead Auburn to a 95-76 win over Temple on Monday night.
article.headline: Bonner's 29, Hobbs' 20 key to Auburn's win over Temple
article.linkText: Bonner, Hobbs power No. 21 Auburn past Temple
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. -- DeWanna Bonner scored a game-high 29 points and Sherell Hobbs added 20 to lead Auburn (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) to a 95-76 win over Temple on Monday night.

Alli Smalley, who jump-started the Tigers with two 3-pointers during a 12-2 run to start the second half, finished with 18 points. Point guard Whitney Boddie added 11 points and seven assists for Auburn, which picked up 16 steals and forced 29 turnovers.

Auburn (2-0) overcame shooting 32 percent from the field (14-of-44) to take a 37-34 lead into halftime.

Shaqwedia Wallace led the Owls (1-1) with 21 points. Shanea Cotton added 17 points and Shenita Landry had 13.
